{{expert-subject|Technology|date=May 2014}} [[File:Building a cabin in forest.jpg|thumb|Lifting a heavy timber with a block and tackle on a tripod.]] '''Lifting equipment''', also known as '''lifting gear''', is a general term for any equipment that can be used to lift loads. This includes [[jack (device)|jack]]s, [[block and tackle]], [[vacuum lift]]s, [[hoist (device)|hoist]]s, rotating [[Screw (simple machine)|screws]], [[gantry crane|gantries]], [[A frame]]s, [[gin pole]]s, [[shear legs]], [[sheerleg]], [[windlass]]es, [[lifting harness]]es, [[fork lift]]s, [[hydraulic lifting pad]]s, [[air lift bag]]s, and [[crane (machine)|crane]]s.
Lifting equipment can be dangerous to use,<ref>'''Heavy Lifting''' [http://www.beyondrigging.com/2014/03/heavy-lifting-vs-risky-lifting/ "''Heavy Lifting vs. Risky Lifting''"]</ref> and is the subject of [[safety regulations]] in most countries
