The '''Pattern Oriented Rule Implementation''' ('''PORI''') table is a [[data structure]] invented by [[Amdocs]] for representation of algorithms for determining a price or set of prices in a financial transaction. The PORI table is used to describe the pricing logic associated with the input event. The PORI table enables business analysts to build a language to describe the business logic associated with financial pricing. The pricing logic is composed without the need for [[Computer programming|programming]], and transformed into [[executable]] code using the PORI Core Processor execution engine. The unique PORI representation, and the [[inference engine]] for executing the PORI rules, is used to compute a variety of pricing problems on the input event in [[Real-time computing|real-time]] fashion.

